
Structure of Java Program


1. Class name and .java file name same hona chahiye.
for eg : Demo.java file mein Demo class honi chahiye. tabhi program chlega.

2. Class Name capital alpabet se start krna chahiye.
eg : class Demo

3. “javac Demo.java” will compile the program and create Byte code. yea command chlane pr “Demo.class” file bnn jayegi jis mein Byte code hoga.
4. “java Demo” by this JVM will read the byte code and convert it into computer understandable language.(Binary language)

  5.main function se hi program execute hona start hota hai.Java mein main function hona is cumpulsory.

6. public static void main (String[ ] args)

- [ ] public : public means pure program mein khi se bhi yea block of code use kr sakein.

Abb “main” itna important function hai so we definately want ki main public ho.

- [ ] static : Abb we know , class k objects hote hain. objects ki help se hi hum functions wgera execute krte hain.

But abb main function chlana hai. main function chlane se pehle uss class ka object kaise bnayein jiss mein main function pdaa hai??

Object bina bnaye hi chl jaye main , so hum ne main function ko static rakh liya.

Static variables and functions are the ones which are not dependent on class object to be executed.

static kr dene se abb “main” function ko object ki jrurat nhi to run.

- [ ] void : void is return type of the function.

- [ ] main : function name

- [ ] (String[ ] args) : Arguments / command-line arguments

Strings[ ] -> This is array
Collection of Strings

abb jo arguments hum terminal se denge , as an array it will store in this variable “args”.

eg :
Program
	System.out.println("Hello World!!!");
	System.out.println( args[0] );
        System.out.println( args[1] );

In Terminal
	javac Demo.java
	java Demo 30 “Sanchit”
(yhaa 30 and “Sanchit” arguments hain jo command line mtlb terminal se pass kiya hain direct)

Output :
Hello World!!!
30
Sanchit


